(40, 6, 33, 20, 2, 1, 9, 'seek ye first the kingdom of God', 'Seeking Wisdom and Righteousness', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of seeking wisdom and righteousness. Matthew 6:33 encourages seeking the kingdom of God and His righteousness, while Proverbs 2:1-9 highlights the pursuit of wisdom and understanding as essential for knowing God.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 6, 33, 20, 3, 9, 10, 'seek ye first the kingdom of God', 'Seeking God and Honoring Him', 'Both passages emphasize prioritizing God in one''s life. Matthew 6:33 encourages seeking God''s kingdom first, while Proverbs 3:9-10 highlights honoring the Lord with one''s substance. This connection highlights the principle that placing God first leads to blessings.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 6, 33, 40, 5, 6, 6, 'his righteousness', 'Connection of Righteousness and Fulfillment', 'Both passages emphasize the pursuit of righteousness. Matthew 6:33 encourages seeking God''s kingdom and righteousness, while Matthew 5:6 highlights the blessing for those who hunger and thirst for righteousness.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 6, 33, 40, 19, 29, 29, 'kingdom of God', 'Seeking God''s Kingdom and Rewards', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of prioritizing God and His kingdom. Matthew 6:33 highlights seeking God''s kingdom first, while Matthew 19:29 promises rewards for those who forsake worldly ties for His sake.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 6, 34, 40, 6, 25, 25, NULL, 'Connection of Worry and Provision', 'Both passages emphasize the idea of not worrying about daily needs. They highlight the importance of focusing on the present rather than being anxious about the future.', 'theme', 0.804, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 6, 34, 43, 14, 27, 27, NULL, 'Connection of Peace and Worry', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of not being troubled by future concerns. Matthew encourages not to worry about tomorrow, while John offers peace to alleviate such troubles.', 'theme', 0.699, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 6, 34, 58, 13, 5, 6, 'Take therefore no thought for the morrow', 'Contentment and Trust in God', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of not worrying about the future and being content with what one has. They highlight reliance on God for support and assurance in daily life.', 'theme', 0.6779999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 6, 34, 43, 16, 33, 33, 'sufficient unto the day is the evil thereof', 'Peace Amidst Daily Struggles', 'Both passages emphasize the challenges of daily life. Matthew speaks of the troubles of each day, while John assures believers of peace despite tribulation.', 'theme', 0.615, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 6, 34, 42, 11, 3, 3, 'Sufficient unto the day is the evil thereof', 'Daily Dependence on God', 'Both passages emphasize reliance on God for daily needs. Matthew 6:34 encourages not worrying about tomorrow, while Luke 11:3 requests daily sustenance.', 'theme', 0.538, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 6, 34, 25, 3, 23, 23, 'Sufficient unto the day is the evil thereof', 'Daily Renewal and Faithfulness', 'This connection highlights the theme of daily reliance on God''s provision. Both passages emphasize the importance of focusing on the present day and recognize the renewal that comes each morning.', 'theme', 0.5309999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 6, 34, 11, 17, 14, 16, 'Take therefore no thought for the morrow', 'Provision and Daily Needs', 'Both passages emphasize God''s provision for daily needs. Matthew 6:34 encourages reliance on God for tomorrow, while 1 Kings 17:14-16 illustrates God''s faithfulness in providing sustenance without fail.', 'theme', 0.496, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 7, 1, 42, 6, 37, 37, 'Judge not, that ye be not judged.', 'Connection of Non-Judgment', 'Both passages emphasize the principle of not judging others to avoid being judged. They highlight a reciprocal relationship between judgment and forgiveness.', 'theme', 0.944, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 7, 1, 45, 2, 1, 2, 'Judge not, that ye be not judged.', 'Judgment and Self-Condemnation', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of judgment and its consequences. Matthew warns against judging others to avoid being judged, while Romans highlights that judging others leads to self-condemnation.', 'theme', 0.7969999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 7, 1, 59, 4, 11, 12, 'Judge not, that ye be not judged.', 'Judgment and Law Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of refraining from judgment. Matthew warns against judging others to avoid being judged, while James elaborates on the implications of speaking evil and judging one''s brother, indicating that such actions challenge the law itself.', 'theme', 0.706, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 7, 1, 45, 14, 10, 13, 'Judge not, that ye be not judged.', 'Judgment and Accountability', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of refraining from judgment of others, highlighting that each individual will ultimately be accountable to God. This connection underscores the theme of personal responsibility in the context of community relationships.', 'theme', 0.643, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 7, 1, 40, 7, 5, 5, 'Judge not, that ye be not judged.', 'Judgment and Hypocrisy Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of judgment and self-examination. Both passages emphasize the importance of addressing one''s own faults before judging others.', 'theme', 0.629, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 7, 1, 46, 4, 3, 5, 'Judge not, that ye be not judged.', 'Judgment and Divine Authority', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of judgment, cautioning against human judgment and highlighting that ultimate judgment belongs to the Lord. This connection illustrates the importance of refraining from premature judgments until divine revelation occurs.', 'theme', 0.566, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 7, 1, 26, 16, 52, 56, 'Judge not, that ye be not judged.', 'Judgment and Shame in Context', 'This connection highlights the theme of judgment and the consequences of self-righteousness. Both passages emphasize the danger of judging others while failing to recognize one''s own faults, as seen in Ezekiel''s call to bear shame for judging others. The phrase ''judge not'' resonates with the admonition in Ezekiel to acknowledge one''s own sins.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 7, 2, 59, 2, 13, 13, 'with what judgment ye judge', 'Judgment and Mercy Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the reciprocal nature of judgment and mercy. Matthew highlights that the measure of judgment reflects back on the judge, while James warns that those who show no mercy will face judgment without mercy.', 'theme', 0.475, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 7, 2, 41, 4, 24, 24, 'with what measure ye mete', 'Judgment and Measure Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the principle of reciprocity in judgment and measurement. The phrase ''with what measure ye mete'' appears in both, linking the concepts of judgment and the consequences of one''s actions.', 'keyword', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 7, 2, 42, 6, 38, 38, 'with what measure ye mete', 'Judgment and Measure Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the principle of reciprocity in judgment and giving. They highlight that the measure one uses will be the same measure applied to them.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 7, 2, 31, 1, 15, 15, NULL, 'Judgment and Retribution Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the principle of reciprocal judgment. Matthew 7:2 states that the measure used in judgment will be applied to the judge, while Obadiah 1:15 declares that actions will return upon the doer, highlighting a theme of divine justice.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 7, 2, 19, 18, 25, 26, 'with what judgment ye judge', 'Judgment and Mercy Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the principle of reciprocity in judgment and mercy. Matthew 7:2 speaks of being judged by the same measure one uses, while Psalms 18:25-26 highlights that one''s treatment of others reflects back on oneself.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 7, 2, 66, 18, 6, 6, 'with what judgment ye judge', 'Judgment and Reward Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the principle of reciprocal judgment and reward. Matthew 7:2 states that the measure used in judgment will be applied to the judge, while Revelation 18:6 reflects this by indicating that the rewards given will be proportional to one''s actions.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 7, 2, 7, 1, 7, 7, 'with what judgment ye judge', 'Judgment and Retribution Theme', 'This connection highlights the theme of retribution, where Adoni-bezek acknowledges that he has received judgment in accordance with his actions. Both passages emphasize the principle that the measure of judgment one applies will be reflected back upon them.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 7, 3, 43, 8, 7, 9, 'considerest not the beam that is in thine own eye', 'Judgment and Self-Reflection', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of self-examination before judging others. Matthew highlights the need to address one''s own faults, while John illustrates how individuals recognized their own sinfulness before condemning another.', 'theme', 0.538, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 7, 3, 48, 6, 1, 1, 'considerest not the beam that is in thine own eye', 'Self-Examination in Restoration', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of self-reflection before addressing others'' faults. Matthew highlights the need to consider one''s own shortcomings, while Galatians advises restoring others with humility, considering one''s own vulnerabilities.', 'theme', 0.51, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 7, 3, 42, 6, 41, 42, 'mote that is in thy brother's eye', 'Connection of Eye Motif', 'Both passages emphasize the contrast between the mote and the beam in one''s eye, highlighting the hypocrisy of judging others while ignoring one''s own faults. This connection illustrates a shared theme of self-examination before addressing the issues of others.', 'theme', 0.475, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 7, 3, 10, 12, 5, 6, NULL, 'Judgment and Self-Reflection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of self-awareness in judgment. In Matthew, the focus is on recognizing one''s own faults before criticizing others, while in 2 Samuel, David''s anger blinds him to his own wrongdoing despite condemning another.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 7, 3, 42, 18, 11, 11, 'considerest not the beam that is in thine own eye', 'Self-Righteousness and Judgment', 'Both passages emphasize the tendency to focus on others'' faults while ignoring one''s own shortcomings. The Pharisee in Luke expresses pride in his righteousness, paralleling the admonition in Matthew to consider one''s own issues first.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
